For sake of integrity it is said, that this software uses following libraries:
1) libzbar 0.10
2) libqrencode 3.9.0
3) quirc 1.0
4) winpthreads (windows build only)
5) musl libc (linux build only)

Zbar and qrencode library are under LGPL license. Thus they have to be built as
dynamic libraries, and they are.

Texts of libraries' licenses are in the "licenses" directory:
LGPL.txt is for libzbar and libqrencode,
winpthread_license.txt is for winpthreads (https://sourceforge.net/p/mingw-w64/code/6184/tree/trunk/mingw-w64-libraries/winpthreads/COPYING),
musl_copyright.txt is for musl libc.

Links for getting libraries' source code:
www.github.com/ZBar
www.fukuchi.org/works/qrencode
www.github.com/dlbeer/quirc
www.musl-libc.org

Windows versions of the software are built with mingw32-w64 cross compiler.
The software can run on Windows XP or higher.

Linux versions of the software are build with musl based gcc cross compiler,
and should work on any linux platform. However, these were only tested on
Ubuntu 16.04.
